    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY - FUEL PUMP CAM INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>FUEL PUMP CAM INSTALLATION</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the camshaft gear, spacer and fuel pump cam were removed without removing the camshaft as
                    described under "Fuel Pump Cam Removal", they must be reinstalled as follows:
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat spacer, fuel pump cam and camshaft gear with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install thrust flange spacer against thrust flange on camshaft using the sleeve (part of
                <emph type="bold">SE4156</emph>) in conjunction with
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE1900-69</emph>
                "Damper/ Crank/Cam Gear Installer". Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350420">4.20</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A thrust bearing is used under the forcing screw to reduce friction.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350418" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11228" filename="../figcg1/CG11228.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.18 Removing Fuel Pump Cam Using SE-4156 Puller</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350419" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12339" filename="../figcg1/CG12339.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.19 Removing Thrust Flange Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350420" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12340a" filename="../figcg1/CG12340A.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.20 Installing Thrust Flange Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>INSTALL WOODRUFF KEY (7, FIGURE
                        <hotlnk document="e435_58.xml" xrefid="ef4350401">4.1</hotlnk>) IN CAMSHAFT PRIOR TO
                        INSTALLATION FUEL PUMP CAM. THIS ASSURES PROPER ORIENTATION OF CAM.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel pump cam lobe against thrust flange spacer on camshaft by aligning keyways on
                fuel pump cam lobe with key in camshaft. Use
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE1900-69</emph>
                "Damper/Crank/Cam Gear Installer" and sleeve (part of
                <emph type="bold">SE4156</emph>) in a manner similar to steps 1 and 2.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install camshaft gear over woodruff key, against fuel pump cam lobe on camshaft using
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE1900-69</emph>
                with large diameter sleeve and thrust bearing as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_78.xml" xrefid="ef4350421">4.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Assemble with timing marks on the front side of the gear. Align timing marks with crankshaft
                        gear marks. Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_78.xml" xrefid="ef4350421">4.21</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install camshaft washer (
                <emph type="bold">2, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_58.xml" xrefid="ef4350401">4.1</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and screw (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_58.xml" xrefid="ef4350401">4.1</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                )
                <emph type="bold"></emph>then tighten to specified torque. (See
                <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350402.xml" xrefid="hl4350402">SPECIAL TORQUES</hotlnk>.)
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
